Detailed Description

Structure for setting callback function parameters.

struct Fvid2_DrvCbParams_t

Field Documentation

void* Fvid2_DrvCbParams_t::errList

Pointer to a valid framelist or processlist where the driver copies the aborted/error packet.

Fdm_CbFxn Fvid2_DrvCbParams_t::fdmCbFxn

FDM callback function used by the driver to initimate any operation has completed or not.

Ptr Fvid2_DrvCbParams_t::fdmData

FDM specific data which is returned in the callback function as it is.

Fdm_ErrCbFxn Fvid2_DrvCbParams_t::fdmErrCbFxn

FDM error callback function used by the driver to initimate any error occuring at the time of streaming.

Fvid2_Handle Fvid2_DrvCbParams_t::handle

FDM layer FVID2 handle. This can be used by the actual driver to call application callback with proper FVID2 handle instead of routining the call through FDM layer.

Ptr Fvid2_DrvCbParams_t::reserved

For future use. Not used currently. Set this to NULL.
